[2] Guinea: 95 new cases
Date: Thu 19 Mar 2015
Source: Pulse.ng [edited]
http://pulse.ng/health/in-guinea-95-new-ebola-cases-confirmed-id3582236.html


The New York Times reports 95 new cases of Ebola have been confirmed in Guinea in the week that ended [Sun 15 Mar 2015]. This is the highest weekly total for the country so far this year.

Meanwhile Sierra Leone and Liberia continued to show improvements for the week; Sierra Leone reported 55 confirmed new cases which was the country's lowest weekly total since last June [2014].

Liberia on the hand continues its countdown to being an Ebola-free country as the country recorded no new confirmed cases for the 3rd consecutive week. 42 days, after the last negative test is done, must elapse before transmission of the highly contagious Ebola virus is considered to have ended in Liberia. [But note below, sadly a case of Ebola was confirmed in Liberia 20 Mar 2015. - Mod.LK]

A total of 10 154 people have died from the Ebola epidemic so far, with the most mortalities recorded in Liberia, Guinea, and Sierra Leone.

[Byline: Onnaedo Okafor]

