[5] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention
21 Mar 2015 Ghana: Ebola -- 42 Ghanaian health workers quarantined in Ivory Coast
http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=351354
[The 42 health-care [HC] worker volunteers in Sierra Leone are quarantined in [Ivory Coast]. They are due back home today [21 Mar 2015], but must first undergo the required 21-day screening program in Ivory Coast before they will be allowed to enter the country. There are no indications any of the HC workers have contracted Ebola]

20 Mar 2015 Liberia official: new patient tests positive for Ebola
http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/A/AF_EBOLA_WEST_AFRICA?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2015-03-20-13-32-23
[The woman has been transferred to an Ebola treatment center in Monrovia. It is unclear where or from whom she became infected (see post below). This new infection appeared 3 weeks after the last Ebola-positive patient in Liberia was discharged home.]

21 Mar 2015: Dismay as Liberia reports 1st new Ebola infection in month
http://www.nation.co.ke/news/africa/Dismay-as-Liberia-reports-first-new-Ebola-infection-in-month/-/1066/2661622/-/10bldxf/-/index.html
[It is not clear where or how she contracted the Ebola virus. A source close to the case, speaking to AFP (Agence France-Presse) on condition of anonymity, said the woman was the wife of a cured Ebola patient. According to experts, a patient can still transmit the virus through sex days after being cured. Continued resistance within communities in Sierra Leone and Guinea to measures taken to deal with the outbreak is threatening progress. In both countries some infected with Ebola are not being isolated and treated, and some unsafe burials are still occurring.]

20 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: African Minerals non-exec resigns
http://awoko.org/2015/03/20/sierra-leone-news-african-minerals-non-exec-resigns/
[One of the Directors of African Minerals who, on Wed 18 Mar 2015, was nominated by the Chinese-owned Shandong Iron and Steel Group (SISG), has resigned his position, effective immediately]

22 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: president orders Ebola lockdown
http://www.3news.co.nz/world/sierra-leone-president-orders-ebola-lockdown-2015032207
[President Koroma has ordered Sierra Leone's entire population to stay in their homes for 3 days (27 Mar 2015 to 29 Mar 2015) in an attempt to contain the spread of the Ebola epidemic. According to Koroma, there will be "no trading activities across the country." Authorities in the Muslim-majority state will lift the lockdown for part of the day to allow church services on Palm Sunday]

