Technology
----------
20 Mar 2015: 'Ebola-proof' tablet to shield medics from deadly virus
http://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-ebola-proof-tablet-to-shield-medics-from-deadly-virus-2070508
[Innovation at work -- According to the BBC (http://www.dnaindia.com/world/report-ebola-proof-tablet-to-shield-medics-from-deadly-virus-2070508) [edited], the tablet, which was designed by technology volunteers and Google, can be used even wearing gloves and in storms and high humidity. It can be dunked in 0.5 percent chlorine solution which kills Ebola. Sharp edges of the tablet were removed so that protective clothing would not be pierced. - Mod.LK]

